variable.name: raw1
variable.description: Tumor Necrosis Factor Receptor II raw OD reading for first well

variable.name: blcor1
variable.description: Tumor Necrosis Factor Receptor II baseline corrected OD reading for first well

variable.name: conc1
variable.description: Tumor Necrosis Factor Receptor II concentration for first well
variable.comment: If CONC1 was less than or equal to the lowest detectable limit of 0.6 pg/ml, then CONC1 was set to 0.6 pg/ml.

variable.name: raw2
variable.description: Tumor Necrosis Factor Receptor II raw OD reading for second well

variable.name: blcor2
variable.description: Tumor Necrosis Factor Receptor II baseline corrected OD reading for second well

variable.name: conc2
variable.description: Tumor Necrosis Factor Receptor II concentration for second well
variable.comment: If CONC2 was less than or equal to the lowest detectable limit of 0.6 pg/ml, then CONC2 was set to 0.6 pg/ml.
variable.value: Unknown or only run in singleton

variable.name: mresult
variable.description: Tumor Necrosis Factor Receptor II mean concentration
variable.comment: The mean result was only calculated if the sample was done in duplicate. To keep results consistent, the first concentration was used as the final TNFR reading for all samples (Variable TNFR).

variable.name: tnfr
variable.description: Tumor Necrosis Factor Receptor II concentration
variable.comment: For flag = 1, 2 or 3, TNFR is the same as CONC1 regardless of whether the sample was done in duplicate or not. If TNFR was less than or equal to the lowest detectable limit of 0.6 pg/ml, then TNFR was set to 0.6 pg/ml. 1038.90 - 29,375.66 FOR FLAG = 1; 1089.34 - 948,113.88 FOR FLAG = 2; 1144.13 - 533,720.64 FOR FLAG = 3

variable.name: flag
variable.comment: When doing analysis, use the variable TNFR where flag = 1 and 2. Phantoms have their FHS ID number listed under IDTYPE and ID, with their phantom id number listed under PHANTOM_ID. When looking at phantom samples, use flag = 3 records as well as their corresponding FHS ID numbers in either flag = 1 or 2.
variable.value: FHS samples that can be used for analysis, done in singleton
FHS samples that can be used for analysis, done in duplicate
